        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Utilizing a Cache as a session saveHandler is like having a saveHandler as a database except a bit more flexible.\r\n\r\nThe cache supports the Zend_Cache_Core frontend and any backend attached to it.\r\nThis becomes extremely valuable for things like Memcache \/ Memcached.  In a development environment we have even used APC.\r\n\r\nAttached is a patch for this improvement that contains the SaveHandler support and tests.\r\n\r\nThe files are as follows:\r\nM       tests\/Zend\/Session\/SaveHandler\/AllTests.php\r\nA       tests\/Zend\/Session\/SaveHandler\/CacheTest.php\r\nA       library\/Zend\/Session\/SaveHandler\/Cache.php"
        },
